2.title: Dangerous Durnin
2.plot: FidoTV Channel: Kim and Trent are worried. One-year-old Durnin has ripped up their couch, chewed pipes and wires, destroyed Kim's shoes, and jumps dangerously against the glass doors. This chocolate Lab puppy is almost full grown. If it doesn't change soon, it could endanger Kim and Trent's most precious thing of all, their three-month-old baby! Family-friendly FidoTV focuses on dogs and canines.

3.title: No Horsing Around
3.plot: FidoTV Channel: Chai, a lovable Pomeranian cross puppy, is a real Jekyll and Hyde. Inside, he appears fearful and pees everywhere. But outside, he barks and chases his family's prize-winning horses, threatening the family business and his own safety. Can Mac, Amanda and their four girls turn this tiny terror into the family pet they all wanted? FidoTV is a family-friendly channel focused on dogs.

4.title: The Sky Is Falling
4.plot: FidoTV Channel: Sky is a beautiful Husky puppy whose bad behavior has her family declaring a disaster! Her howling, jumping, and accidents leave them arguing, frustrated and living behind a barricade of baby gates. Dad Wade threatens to get rid of Sky if things don't change. Can they work as a team to keep Sky in the picture? FidoTV is a family-friendly channel focused on dogs and canine pets.

5.title: Hot Cocoa
5.plot: FidoTV Channel: Cocoa the Chihuahua is in hot water! She jumps up on the couch, up on the windowsill, and into purses, snatches food, barks nonstop, and shreds money. This puppy jumps everywhere but into the arms of her owner 13-year-old Jordan whom she bites instead! If he can't control her soon, she'll be jumping into a new home! Family-friendly FidoTV focuses on dogs and canine animal pets.

6.title: Putting Pedro in His Place
6.plot: FidoTV Channel: Pedro is a 5-month-old Chihuahua puppy with an attitude. He's domineering, loud, and tends to bite, which has forced his family to put their social life on hold. Their other Chihuahua Lola is completely laid back, so where did they go wrong? FidoTV is a family-friendly channel focused on dogs and canine animal pets.

7.title: Big Bad Stella
7.plot: FidoTV Channel: She's not even 8 months old but Stella the Bull Mastiff is a big puppy powerhouse! That's big trouble for her owner Sasheena, who has back issues and risks real injury if she's pulled. The four kids are too small to manage Stella. If this lovable big puppy doesn't learn some manners she has an uncertain future. Family-friendly FidoTV focuses on dogs and canine animal pets.

8.title: Pug Puppy Pandemonium
8.plot: FidoTV Channel: Chain is a tiny, adorable 8-week-old Pug in a brand new home, yet the chaos has already begun! He's starting to chew, nip, and isn't interested in house training. His extended family doesn't know where to start with fixing him. They have another shock when they realize how much control this tenacious pup already has. Family-friendly FidoTV focuses on dogs and canine animal pets.

9.title: When Opposites Don't Attract
9.plot: FidoTV: Aspen is a mix of American Eskimo (bred for extreme cold) and Chihuahua (bred for the extreme heat). When opposite breeds come together in this tiny puppy, it creates huge problems! Brandon threatens to leave if this yapping puppy stays; his sister won't stay if her puppy goes. A once-happy family may break up if things don't change fast! Family-friendly FidoTV Channel focuses on dogs.

10.title: Sadie on Patrol
10.plot: FidoTV Channel: Alan, Christy and their teenage daughters live on a beautiful apple orchard. Their Bernese/Retriever puppy Sadie is tasked to be a natural alarm when predators like bears, coyotes, and cougars pass through. But Sadie is a runner and resists all forms of control. Can this family bond with Sadie to ensure safety for them all? Family-friendly FidoTV focuses on dogs and canine pets.

13.title: Who's Harley?
13.plot: FidoTV Channel: Named after a motorcycle, raised by a cat, and treated like a baby dressed in diapers and doll clothes, this is one screwed-up puppy! At 10 months old, this Bichon Frise now thinks he's a cat and can't go anywhere without his diapers. Is it too late to save this puppy from an identity crisis? Family-friendly FidoTV focuses on dogs and canine animal pets.

imdb.plot outline: A cute puppy can be the perfect family addition. What's not to love? Her fluffy fur and soul-stirring eyes are just too cute. Five months later, the honeymoon is over... way over, and the novelty of the new puppy has worn off. In her place is a hairy little monster that bites, pees everywhere, and chews on all the furniture, creating tension within the family. A once harmonious home is now in domestic meltdown! It's time to bring in Brad Pattison, a dog behaviourist and life coach, who is widely known for his tough love techniques and crazy antics. He's the consummate dog lover and ultimate trainer-firm but gentle. In this fast-paced series, monster mutts are transformed into darling dogs, all while restoring peace within the family.
